<subSubSection id="B58AC850B726049984F631F06FF408F1" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="B7DAE25F4AF660E004783FB00819167B" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<taxonomicName id="55C575E6F1881DFF76EBFBB0404C286E" class="Arachnida" family="Brachychthoniidae" genus="Brachychthonius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perpusillus">Brachychthonius perpusillus Berlese</taxonomicName>
, 1910, p. 220, pl. 19 fig. 41; Lombardini, 1936, p. 38; Forsslund, 1942, p. 4, fig. 4; 1957, p. 590, fig. 12.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8D9E8478CD02B51E3628ACA4F505BEC8" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="EC14E666A202BB24CAF1424273D8E473" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
Forsslund (1957) recently established the identity of the present species; the holotype conforms to the Swedish specimens described by him as 
<taxonomicName id="850C2544DC887F19E68844EB2A9877DB" class="Arachnida" family="Brachychthoniidae" genus="Brachychthonius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perpusillus">Brachychthonius perpusillus</taxonomicName>
in 1942. I do not know if 
<taxonomicName id="A078F49042A04265FB4FAD852DD469AE" class="Arachnida" family="Hypochthoniidae" genus="Hypochthonius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevis">Hypochthonius brevis Michael</taxonomicName>
is identical with 
<taxonomicName id="6FB33C35E61AB233DE3BCE50EA89C206" class="Arachnida" family="Brachychthoniidae" genus="Brachychthonius" genus.bestMatchDistance="48" genus.bestMatchVote="2" genus.innerRound="1" genus.outerRound="1" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perpusillus">B. perpusillus</taxonomicName>
; it is at least a closely related species that belongs to the genus 
<taxonomicName id="0D964AD404A09B0EDD104E4E6E0F0582" class="Arachnida" family="Brachychthoniidae" genus="Liochthonius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Liochthonius</taxonomicName>
(cf. Evans, 1952, p. 227).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C039031846068AA2E80E37D3DDF025AE" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="3BBA1903082576DFA2317FC7C6A1FEE9" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<taxonomicName id="7ED50A837F701A8EA241C6B7AA494D72" class="Arachnida" family="Brachychthoniidae" genus="Brachychthonius" genus.bestMatchDistance="117" genus.bestMatchVote="2" genus.innerRound="1" genus.outerRound="1" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perpusillus">B. perpusillus</taxonomicName>
occurs in Europe and North America; Berlese collected a heterogenous collection of specimens in Tuscany and North Italy; Forsslund (1957) designated slide no. 72/41 as holotype.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
